CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 2, 1957, pg. 1, reads: "BIAS CASE DISMISSED - After Robert Zadrowski (party obscured) and Henry Mitchell (center) testified that Alfred J. Veshio (left) was not the bartender who denied them service at Sewickley's Town House and Bar. Alderman Harry B. Fitzgerald (right, with glasses), who heard Veshio maintain that he was the bartender, dismissed the case as one of mistaken identity at a Monday night session. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Robert Zadrowski, Henry Mitchell, and Alfred J. Veshio testifying in front of Alderman Harry B. Fitzgerald in discrimination case
